text: Harry Frederick Pollock was Liberal Unionist Party MP for Spalding. He contested the seat in 1892, won it in 1895, but lost it to the Liberals in 1900. ==Sources== *Craig, F.W.S. British Parliamentary Election Results 1885-1918 *Whitaker's Almanack, 1893 to 1906 editions Category:Liberal Unionist Party MPs for English constituencies Category:UK MPs 1895–1900 Category:Politics of Lincolnshire
title: Harry Frederick Pollock
